
>> I am cleaning up the house. I see that the shoes need to be put away. I will: 1)
 take the shoes upstairs to the closet 2) put away the shoes. (Done, done.)
This is one of the best ways I’ve developed to remember what I need to do. When I’ve finished something, I can cross it off the list and feel a sense of accomplishment. But when I have to write everything out, I feel like a robot